repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

commit.message: Detect and remove useless "@substitute: naming" tags in utility code.
Refactor the utility code macros to make them more extensible.
Add a new utility code macro "EMPTY(bytes|tuple|...)" to inject references to empty Python constants.
Move non-methods out of the class scope.
Remove useless "@substitute: naming" tag in utility code.
Fix the "common include dir" feature by correctly checking if the utility code is module specific (and by actually making "AddTraceback()" module agnostic again).
Avoid a bit of overhead in test code.
Enable the "common_include_dir" test on Windows since it should generally work there.
Disable multiprocessing on win32 in "common_include_dir" test since it seems to hang.
Tests: Exclude "common_include_dir" test on Windows again as long as it does not succeed there.
The C names of empty collection constants (tuple/bytes/str) are actually not module specific and thus should not prevent sharing include files.
Revert the change in AddTraceback() since we no longer consider the code module specific.

milestone.description:
* Remove code for Python 2 and Python < 3.7.
* Integrate better with Python 3.
* Improve support for the Limited API.
* Start supporting GIL-free Python 3.13.
* Support the Py3.13 `sys.monitoring` API.
* Support and use `am_send` for coroutines.
